trans-unit.source: Trading Partner Management Object Model: REST Endpoint
trans-unit.target: Trading Partner Management Object Model: REST Endpoint

trans-unit.source: REST endpoint used for the TPM OM APIs.
trans-unit.target: REST endpoint used for the TPM OM APIs.

trans-unit.source: After you have provisioned your BizTalk Service (steps at <externalLink><linkText>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=299821</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=299821</linkUri></externalLink>), a deployment URL is created for your environment.
trans-unit.target: After you have provisioned your BizTalk Service (steps at <externalLink><linkText>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=299821</linkText><linkUri>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=299821</linkUri></externalLink>), a deployment URL is created for your environment.

trans-unit.source: You can use that URL to arrive at the REST endpoint used for the TPM OM APIs.
trans-unit.target: You can use that URL to arrive at the REST endpoint used for the TPM OM APIs.

trans-unit.source: TPM OM API uses the <codeInline>$metadata</codeInline> operation to make the entities discoverable.
trans-unit.target: TPM OM API uses the <codeInline>$metadata</codeInline> operation to make the entities discoverable.

trans-unit.source: The URI to retrieve the metadata is:
trans-unit.target: The URI to retrieve the metadata is:

trans-unit.source: Here, <legacyItalic><base_URL></legacyItalic> refers to the deployment URL of the <token>af_integration</token> environment.
trans-unit.target: Here, <legacyItalic><base_URL></legacyItalic> refers to the deployment URL of the <token>af_integration</token> environment.

trans-unit.source: For example, if the deployment URL is <codeInline>https://mybiztalkservice.biztalk.windows.net</codeInline>, the URL to retrieve the metadata should be <codeInline>https://mybiztalkservice.biztalk.windows.net/default/$PartnerManagement/$metadata</codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: For example, if the deployment URL is <codeInline>https://mybiztalkservice.biztalk.windows.net</codeInline>, the URL to retrieve the metadata should be <codeInline>https://mybiztalkservice.biztalk.windows.net/default/$PartnerManagement/$metadata</codeInline>.

trans-unit.source: This URL allows you to retrieve all valid entity types, entity properties, associations, and so on.
trans-unit.target: This URL allows you to retrieve all valid entity types, entity properties, associations, and so on.

trans-unit.source: You can also view the metadata by hitting the endpoint in a browser.
trans-unit.target: You can also view the metadata by hitting the endpoint in a browser.

trans-unit.source: TPM OM API: What to do Where?
trans-unit.target: TPM OM API: What to do Where?

trans-unit.source: The TPM OM API enables users to write applications to create and manage the entities required in business-to-business messaging.
trans-unit.target: The TPM OM API enables users to write applications to create and manage the entities required in business-to-business messaging.

trans-unit.source: While the object model aims to have complete parity with the operations available through the portal, there are some tasks that are done outside the use of the object model.
trans-unit.target: While the object model aims to have complete parity with the operations available through the portal, there are some tasks that are done outside the use of the object model.

trans-unit.source: This section provides information on the tasks that can be performed using the object model, the tasks that can be performed using the <link xlink:href="381e888e-1289-4cc2-a2fa-58128379d72c" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure BizTalk Services PowerShell CmdLets</link>, and the tasks that can be performed using the <token>tpm_portal</token>.
trans-unit.target: This section provides information on the tasks that can be performed using the object model, the tasks that can be performed using the <link xlink:href="381e888e-1289-4cc2-a2fa-58128379d72c" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Azure BizTalk Services PowerShell CmdLets</link>, and the tasks that can be performed using the <token>tpm_portal</token>.

trans-unit.source: Connecting to the TPM OM API REST Endpoint
trans-unit.target: Connecting to the TPM OM API REST Endpoint

trans-unit.source: To retrieve the metadata about TPM OM entities, you can simply hit the endpoint in a browser.
trans-unit.target: To retrieve the metadata about TPM OM entities, you can simply hit the endpoint in a browser.

trans-unit.source: However, if you want to perform any CRUD operations on the entities, you must request messages that include the required header values as well as message payload (if required).
trans-unit.target: However, if you want to perform any CRUD operations on the entities, you must request messages that include the required header values as well as message payload (if required).

trans-unit.source: You must include the required headers for invoking the REST endpoint.
trans-unit.target: You must include the required headers for invoking the REST endpoint.

trans-unit.source: TPM OM API enables users to send OData-based HTTP requests to create TPM OM entities and receive responses in verbose JSON, atom+pub, or straight XML.
trans-unit.target: TPM OM API enables users to send OData-based HTTP requests to create TPM OM entities and receive responses in verbose JSON, atom+pub, or straight XML.

trans-unit.source: Because the TPM OM API conforms to <token>azure_2</token> design guidelines, there is a set of required HTTP headers that each client must use when connecting to the TPM OM API REST endpoint, as well as a set of optional headers that can be used.
trans-unit.target: Because the TPM OM API conforms to <token>azure_2</token> design guidelines, there is a set of required HTTP headers that each client must use when connecting to the TPM OM API REST endpoint, as well as a set of optional headers that can be used.

trans-unit.source: The following sections describe the headers and HTTP verbs you can use with the TPM OM API.
trans-unit.target: The following sections describe the headers and HTTP verbs you can use with the TPM OM API.

trans-unit.source: For a list of required and optional headers, see the HTTP Request, HTTP Response, and HTTP Verbs sections (in this topic).
trans-unit.target: For a list of required and optional headers, see the HTTP Request, HTTP Response, and HTTP Verbs sections (in this topic).

trans-unit.source: Wherever applicable, you must include the required property names with appropriate values.

trans-unit.source: Creating .NET Applications Using the TPM OM API
trans-unit.target: Creating .NET Applications Using the TPM OM API

trans-unit.source: Because the TPM OM API is based on the OData protocol, you can use the WCF Data Services to build .NET applications that perform CRUD operations on the entities.
trans-unit.target: Because the TPM OM API is based on the OData protocol, you can use the WCF Data Services to build .NET applications that perform CRUD operations on the entities.

trans-unit.source: For more information on how create .NET applications using the TPM OM API, see <link xlink:href="b1464cb6-685d-47ea-8596-bc4655234fc8" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Creating .NET Applications Using TPM OM REST API</link>.
